`t3-light` and `t3-dark` replicate the existing CSS cascade behavior. Their CSS uses Tailwind v4 internal references (`var(--color-neutral-950)`, `color-mix()`, `--alpha()`) that cannot be set as inline styles. Rather than duplicating them as raw values, these two themes are tagged `cssManaged: true`:

- When active, **no inline CSS overrides** are set — the existing `:root` / `@variant dark` CSS handles it.
- Their `colors` are still populated with representative hex values so the theme selector can render preview swatches.

`t3-midnight` (and any future custom theme) has `cssManaged: false` and uses raw `oklch()` / hex values that are injected as inline styles on `document.documentElement`.

The `ThemeDefinition` interface gains: `readonly cssManaged: boolean`.

